<text id="F8538T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>Thaddeus Stevens offers advice to Edward McPherson on his campaign, including the liberal use of money.</p> 
</div1> 
</front> 

<body id="d4">
<div1 type="letter" id="d5">


<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1858-06-20">June 20 1858</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute>Dear <unclear>Sir</unclear></salute> 
</opener> 

<p>I have taken a long time as in truth I am so pressed as not to know what to do, or when I can pay-- I do not doubt that you are right although I fully believe myself out of this <unclear>responsibility</unclear>.</p>

<p>You are right in letting your friends have their way -- You will have a hard road to
travel-- You must <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> every <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> well and spend your money freely or you have no chance with your desperate appointment--</p>

<closer>
<salute></salute> 
<signed>Thaddeus Stevens</signed> 
<seg type="postscript"> 
<name type="recipient">E. McPherson</name>
</seg>
</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
